  "text": "This section considers uniform flows through an array of rigid vertical emergent cylinders (cases W and W0). It is important to note that, compared with previous studies of cylinder arrays [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , the characteristic length of the bed roughness is of the same order of magnitude as the cylinder diameter in this case: k S =D % 0:7, where k S is the equivalent sand grain size of the bed roughness.",
